So, relation Z in 3NF but not BCNF , becasuse of S is not superkey. Since, this decomposition covers all functional dependencies of original relation (X), so decomposition of X into Y and Z is dependency preserving . Also, this decomposition has common attribute (i.e., R) which is superkey of relation Y(PR), so decomposition of X into Y and Z is also lossless join decomposition . Option (D) is correct.

